The aim of this study is to explore the efficacy of 18F-FSPG in the detection of primary or metastatic brain cancer lesions confirmed by a standard of truth, preferably histology.

 This is a single center, open labelled, non-randomized study.

 A total of 30 subjects with brain tumor or brain metastases will be enrolled.

 All different stages of malignancies will be recruited, including those with different types of pathologies and grades, and newly diagnosed or recurrent disease.

